The paper discusses privacy issues in the cyber-enabled sharing world, which falls under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.CY). The paper also discusses security concerns, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper evaluates existing solutions and identifies hot and cold topics, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses privacy concerns from users', platforms', and service providers' perspectives, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
